quit

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
quit -  A forced quit.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int quit()
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
0 if it failed, non zero if it succeeded.
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/global/player.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

A forced quit.
This is the function called by external objects to quit
a player. It avoids checks for things like being in combat.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
do_quit(), quit_alt(), efun::command()

.EP

